				"id": "http://jnicholson.micro.blog/2022/05/28/setting-up-hugo-on-cloudflare.html",
				"title": "Setting Up Hugo on Cloudflare",
				"content_html": "<p>I wanted to start off by sharing how I set up this my original homepage. I was impressed by how easy it was to do, especially since I&rsquo;m new to both Hugo and Cloudflare Pages.</p>\n<p>I followed the <a href=\"https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/framework-guides/deploy-a-hugo-site/\">excellent documentation</a> that Cloudflare provides. If you&rsquo;re not married to the idea of using Hugo, they also provide great documentation on <a href=\"https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/framework-guides/\">other frameworks</a>.</p>\n<p>One thing I missed the first time I pushed updates to my repo was <a href=\"https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/framework-guides/deploy-a-hugo-site/#using-a-specific-hugo-version\">setting the version of Hugo</a>. The version that Hugo provides is older and didn&rsquo;t work with my chosen theme.</p>\n",
				
				"date_published": "2022-05-27T22:31:19-04:00",
